The objectives of the CCASS are: 
To generate high quality, relevant public health information on birth prevalence and temporal trends of congenital anomalies to inform programs, policies, and public health action;
To develop the minimum data sets and common definitions in order to attain quality and consistency in surveillance activities in Canada;
To facilitate collaborative congenital anomalies surveillance and research efforts among provinces and territories;
To facilitate the communication of information related to congenital anomalies for health professionals and the Canadian public;
To foster educational opportunities in congenital anomalies surveillance and research.

